  ("npc1_morality_speech", "Oy -- boss. Please don't take this the wrong way, but it's a hard life and it's a bit much that we {s21}. Take a little more care in the future, warlord, if you don't mind my saying."),
  ("npc2_morality_speech", "I hope you don't mind my saying so, but it's a bit hard for me to see us {s21}. Maybe I ought to try to be more of a hardened soldier, but if we could try to exercise a little mercy from time to time, I'd sleep better."),
  ("npc3_morality_speech", "Perhaps it is not my place to say so, {sir/madame}, but I confess that I am somewhat shocked that we {s21}. Of course I realize that war is cruel, but there is no need to make it more cruel than necessary."),
  ("npc4_morality_speech", "I beg your pardon, warlord -- just so you know, the men of the House of Gwawrddur do not care to {s21}. I will not be pleased if you continue to take this course."),
  ("npc5_morality_speech", "Pardon me, warlord. It is not good to {s21}. Your first duty is to the men who form your shield-wall. The least they can expect is food, pay, the opportunity to loot, and that you not waste their lives needlessly."),
  ("npc6_morality_speech", "Excuse me, {sir/madame}. As you know, I joined with you to right wrongs, protect the innocent, kill Visigoths, and make amends for my sin. I did not expect to {s21}."),
  ("npc7_morality_speech", "Warlord -- I do not like to see us {s21}. Such are the actions of a common bandit chief, with no regard for his followers."),
  ("npc8_morality_speech", "I was not pleased that you decided to {s21}. To fall in battle is an honor, but to fight in a shield-wall led by a coward is a disgrace."),
  ("npc9_morality_speech", "{Sir/Madame} -- it is not my way to {s21}. Men of my house will accept death but, not dishonor. Please do not make me ashamed to serve under you."),
  ("npc10_morality_speech", "Begging your pardon, warlord. I can't say that I'm happy to see us {s21}. Those are just simple people, trying to make a living. If we could try to go easy on the poor wretches, warlord, I'd feel much better."),
  ("npc11_morality_speech", "Excuse me, {handsome/beauty}. It's not good that we {s21}. The least the soldiers expect of a leader is to feed them, pay them, and do {his/her} best to keep their sorry skins intact as best {he/she} can."),
  ("npc12_morality_speech", "Warlord -- I do not like to see us {s21}. I am prepared to be a warrior, but not a brigand. Pray let us try to show a little more compassion."),
  ("npc13_morality_speech", "I do not care to {s21}. No one with a reputation for cowardice will be properly feared by his men."),
  ("npc14_morality_speech", "Warlord, if we can avoid it, I'd prefer not to {s21}. Britannia is a small place, and one's reputation is precious. I would not care for one of my rivals to include this latest unfortunate incident in a satirical verse."),
  ("npc15_morality_speech", "{Sir/Madame} -- just so you know my opinion, any commander with sense will not let his shield-wall {s21}.I hope you don't mind me speaking so bluntly."),
  ("npc16_morality_speech", "Warlord. I don't like to {s21}. God does not approve of this kind of behavior, it will surely lead you to Hell, if left unchecked by my holy teachings."),
  ("npc_bashe_morality_speech", "I do not care to {s21}. No one with a reputation for blatant cowardice will be properly respected and obeyed by his shield-wall."),
  ("npc_sange_morality_speech", "I do not care to {s21}. No one with a reputation for blatant cowardice will be properly respected and obeyed by his shield-wall."),
  ("npc_paintrain_morality_speech", "Captain. I don't like to {s21}. So many throats left uncut, and so many purses left unexplored..."),
