  ("npc1_personalityclash_speech", "Chief -- no offense, but I'm a bit tired of {s11}, who puts on airs like she's something better than your humble servant, Osmund."), #Osmund-Bridei
  ("npc2_personalityclash_speech", "{Sir/Madame} -- as you recall I was a merchant before I signed on with you. I respect men who make their living peacefully, risking all to bring goods for faraway lands."), #Aleifr-Frioc
  ("npc3_personalityclash_speech", "Warlord -- in my opinion, {s11} is a terrible man. He has tried to seduce me into his bed many times, and I have already seen him following me during the night, when I am alone. I tell you, I am pretty scared of him."), #Eithne-Brian
  ("npc4_personalityclash_speech", "{Sir/Madame}. The House of Gwawrddur is one of the most ancient and respected families in this part of the world, with a provenance dating back to the Roman Empire. Yet {s11} openly shows me disrespect, and always calls me a ridiculous Briton."), #Athwrys-Ceawlin
  ("npc5_personalityclash_speech", "A moment of your time, warlord. {s11} seems to think me a common bandit, just because I have rewarded myself in the past to the legitimate spoils of war from caravans passing through my family's lands."), #Frioc-Aleifr
  ("npc6_personalityclash_speech", "Your pardon, {sir/madame}, but I cannot keep my tongue still any longer. That harlot, {s11} -- every time she sees me, she points the five fingers of her hand at me -- a peasant's sign to ward off evil."), #Bodero-Gwenllian
  ("npc7_personalityclash_speech", "Warlord, I have done my best to put up with your followers' rude talk and filthy habits. But that one who calls himself {s11} is beyond tolerance."), #Bridei-Osmund
  ("npc8_personalityclash_speech", "Just so you know, I cannot abide that insolent {s11}, who likes to call himself a 'philosopher'. That southern rat loves to speak in that awful gibberish talk he calls 'Latin', and loves to laugh at me behind my back because I do not understand what he is saying."), #Siwi-Orosio
  ("npc9_personalityclash_speech", "{Sir/Madame} -- {s11} is a base braggart, a man with as much respect for the bravery of other men as a Visigoth. I am tired of hearing how he and his fellow warriors could defeat anyone in the battlefield, just because he is a master of military discipline."), #Lothar-Liuva
  ("npc10_personalityclash_speech", "Excuse me, warlord. I hate to trouble you with such things, but I just wanted to let you know that I can't abide that fellow Athrwys, he likes to say he is some sort of squire to Gwawrddur or something."), #Ceawlin-Athwrys
  ("npc11_personalityclash_speech", "Begging your pardon, {handsome/beauty}, but I can't keep silent, not to you, my dear. That man, {s11} -- he killed his own brother, and even though he's haunted by his crime, he still loves battle with bloodthirsty passion. He is very dangerous, I think. He has... he has also tried to court me, and has promised to kill a thousand Visigoths in my honor."), #Gwenllian-Bodero
  ("npc12_personalityclash_speech", "My {lord/lady}. That ignorant Frisian, {s11}, has been spreading lies that I am nothing more than a cowardly rascal, unfit for the battlefield. He also said that 'philosopher' is Latin for 'effeminate'. Which_it_isn't._As a man that was educated in the holy city of Rome, I know for a fact that the Latin word for 'effeminate' is 'mollis'."), #Orosio-Siwi
  ("npc13_personalityclash_speech", "Excuse me, warlord. I am very close to killing with my bare hands that insect that calls himself 'Lothar'. That joke of a warrior does not understand how bravery without discipline can only result in defeat and shame."), #Liuva-Lothar
  ("npc14_personalityclash_speech", "Warlord, you must be aware that the ugly girl known as Eithne is a disruptive influence to our men. She complains that I have been trying to seduce her, but that is nothing farther from the truth, for I cannot even stand her smell."), #Brian-Eithne
  ("npc15_personalityclash_speech", "Excuse me. I hope you don't mind me telling you that, in my opinion, the priest {s11} is a danger to the party. He only cares about religion and Hell, and is disrespectful of authority and the basic principles of the military art."), #Agasicles-Aedh
  ("npc16_personalityclash_speech", "Just so you know -- there's something demonic about {s11}. He makes strange scrawlings in the dirt, and mutters to himself all the time before battle."), #Aedh-Agasicles
  ("npc_bashe_personalityclash_speech", "Warlord, I am weary of {s11}, who talks of nothing but warrior codes and feats of arms."),
  ("npc_sange_personalityclash_speech", "Warlord, I am weary of {s11}, who talks of nothing but warrior codes and feats of arms."),
  ("npc_paintrain_personalityclash_speech", "Oy, captain. Just so you know -- there's something funny about {s11}. He makes strange scrawlings in the dirt, and mutters to himself."),
  ("npc_hammertime_personalityclash_speech", "There's something strange about {s11}. I do not like him."),
