  ("npc1_personalityclash_speech_b", "She's a common tracker, just like myself, and she has no right to tell me to keep my distance from her, as she did just now."),  #Osmund-Bridei
  ("npc2_personalityclash_speech_b", "I don't much care to hear {s11} gloat about the caravans he has looted, or plans to loot, he has no respect for good honest trade."), #Aleifr-Frioc
  ("npc3_personalityclash_speech_b", "I know that an army is usually a men's place, but I believe I deserve some respect as well. I am no one's whore. I hope you do not mind me saying so."), #Eithne-Brian
  ("npc4_personalityclash_speech_b", "{Sir/Madame}, these are indeed sorry days if common Saxon folk are allowed to mock Brythonic nobles. That is all."), #Athwrys-Ceawlin
  ("npc5_personalityclash_speech_b", "I told him that if the warrior's way bothers him so much, he should become a priest or a beggar and so not have to worry about such things. I hope you do not mind that I said such things."), #Frioc-Aleifr
  ("npc6_personalityclash_speech_b", "I know the crime I committed was an abomination, but I am seeking repentance, and I deserve better than to be the object of some witch's superstition. I think she has some Visigothic blood. I just thought you should know."), #Bodero-Gwenllian
  ("npc7_personalityclash_speech_b", "I do not care for how he stares at me around the campfire after a meal, as he picks his teeth and drinks his foul beer. What I cannot accept is that he keeps saying that he is a much better tracker than myself, which is obviously false. He is base, ignorant, and a completely idiotic drunkard, that could never compare to me in tracking, nor in anything else. I do not care to travel with such people."), #Bridei-Osmund
  ("npc8_personalityclash_speech_b", " It is true I do not know how to read and write, nor how to speak Latin. But I know much more of life and battle than {s11}, and a great warrior like me should not be mocked by some weak-minded thinker. It was only out of respect for you that I refrained from cutting his throat when I overheard his jokes about me. I thought it only fitting that I should warn you."), #Siwi-Orosio
  ("npc9_personalityclash_speech_b", "So I asked him, if he and his men were so much more disciplined than even Frankish warriors, how come he failed to conquer his Cantabrian enemies and exiled himself among the Britons, a people that he despises? He gave me no reply, his face just turned red, then he cursed me and all of my ancestors, and almost challenged me to a duel. He says he is so disciplined, but I think maybe you should discipline him a little more."), #Lothar-Liuva
  ("npc10_personalityclash_speech_b", "Everyone knows there is no Briton of true noble blood. House of Gwawrddur, my arse! Genuine blue-bloods are never Brythonic, and any Briton who pretends to be blue-blood is simple, foolish, and intolerable. Anyway, I might have said something that was a bit sharp to him a minute ago - something like 'if he is truly a noble, that's probably because his father is a Saxon'. He seemed to take offense, anyway. I just thought you should know."), #Ceawlin-Athwrys
  ("npc11_personalityclash_speech_b", "He's a kinslayer, cursed by Christ, and he'll bring misfortune and sorrow upon us, that's for certain. I don't like being around him and I don't think he should be with us. I have also told him that my heart already belongs to someone else, but he keeps speaking of murdering in my name. I cannot abide him any longer. That's all. Sorry for troubling you {handsome/beauty}."), #Gwenllian-Bodero
  ("npc12_personalityclash_speech_b", "It is not my fault that this stupid barbarian is incapable of understanding the beautiful Roman language, nor that he prefers to die with an infected wound than to be helped by my knowledge of nature and human body. Warlord, I am deeply tired of standing such an ungrateful and ignorant lot."),#Orosio-Siwi
  ("npc13_personalityclash_speech_b", "That chit {s11} saw fit to mock the war-like nature of my people, and even suggested that I am in Britannia only because I was defeated in the battlefield, which, of course, has never happened. I will not have my methods nor my beliefs questioned in front of the men, and I will not serve any dhryten who tolerates such insubordination and stupidity in his shield-wall. Thank you for allowing me to speak my piece."),#Liuva-Lothar
  ("npc14_personalityclash_speech_b", "She is the one that has already tried many times to sneak into my tent during the night, and uses every opportunity to be alone with me, trying to provoke me into something I do not dare to say out loud. Please, explain to that impudent girl that Brian only cares for beautiful women, and would have no business with the likes of her."), #Brian-Eithne
  ("npc15_personalityclash_speech_b", "I heard him preaching to the warriors that our preparations before a battle or a siege are completely innocuous, because victory could only be achieved if it befitted God's will. Even though I also believe in Christ, I know for sure that a pure Christian soul alone never guaranteed victory to any army. I think you should tell him to stop this kind of preaching right now."), #Agasicles-Aedh
  ("npc16_personalityclash_speech_b", "Fearing witchcraft, I asked him about it, and he told me that I should mind my own business. So I had a look in his baggage, and found a heretical Greek book that loosely resembled our Holy Bible. I am sure that the words within it are corrupted, and they were probably written by the Devil himself. I think he's a sorcerer, {sir/madame}, and we should definitely get rid of him for the sake of our immortal souls."), #Aedh-Agasicles
  ("npc_bashe_personalityclash_speech_b", "Valorous deeds are all very well, but they are not the only goals worth pursuing in life. Personally, I never trust any man who has not at least once woken up drunk in a ditch, or been beaten by the slipper of his lover before."), 
  ("npc_sange_personalityclash_speech_b", "Valorous deeds are all very well, but they are not the only goals worth pursuing in life. Personally, I never trust any man who has not at least once woken up drunk in a ditch, or been beaten by the slipper of his lover before."), 
  ("npc_paintrain_personalityclash_speech_b", "I think {s11}'s a sorcerer, {sir/madame}, and if I catch him trying to hex me, he'll have a knife in his throat."),
