  ("npc_enchantress_personalityclash2_speech", "I'm a bit tired of {s11}."),
   
  ("npc1_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I have no interest in becoming a Christian, and, in my opinion, this priest only brings us bad luck. Maybe we should burn him."), #Osmund-Aedh 
  ("npc2_personalityclash2_speech_b", "The enemy was bearing down on us, and he says, 'Step aside, merchant, this is true man's work.' Next time I will step aside, and let him take a spear in the gut."), #Aleifr-Lothar
  ("npc3_personalityclash2_speech_b", "After our last victory I was picking through the slain, and that Frisian called Siwi pushed me aside saying that looting was no job for a simple slave girl that was just allowed to travel with the army. I believe that if I battle alongside the shield-wall, I deserve my share of the loot just like any other warrior. Even though I might be less experienced than the others, I also risked my life."), #Eithne-Siwi
  ("npc4_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I forgave her because she is only an ignorant northern woman, but I plead that you tell her that she is speaking to one of her superiors, and that she must remember her place."),#Athwrys-Bridei
  ("npc5_personalityclash2_speech_b", "As far as I understand she is but a slave. Yet, when I ordered her to fetch me a fine piece of stew last night, she refused and said that I should get it myself. Yesterday I was too tired to properly slap her for her impudence, and so I let it go, but I will not tolerate such disrespect in the future."), #Frioc-Gwenllian
  ("npc6_personalityclash2_speech_b", "My dryhten -- we should not tolerate that Visigothic bastard in our shield-wall. The battle is no place for mockeries, and no true warrior would pester a fallen foe. Please, let me kill this idiot, let me appease my tortured soul with this enemy's blood."), #Bodero-Liuva
  ("npc7_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He also insists that I should address him as 'My Lord', instead of his ridiculous name. I tell you, one day when I have my own band of Pictish warriors, I will hunt him down and ask him how much better a warrior he is with my axe buried in his skull."), #Bridei-Athwrys
  ("npc8_personalityclash2_speech_b", "As we were cleaning our weapons after that last battle, I remarked that I thought her a handsome girl, and after I conquered Frisia, I would happily find her a match with one of my warriors. I explained to her that even though I am looking for a wife, I would only marry a free woman. I thought it was a very generous offer, as an army slave is hardly going to find herself awash in prospects. But rather than thank me, she simply turned her back without a word. It was only out of respect for your leadership that I did not immediately try to teach her some manners. I really think you should discipline your slaves better."), #Siwi-Eithne
  ("npc9_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I appreciate that he is willing to risk his life in battle, but that alone does not make a warrior. He is not of noble birth, and his family's wealth comes from commerce and usury, which is not adequate for a member of a shield-wall. He may fight with us as an auxiliary, as a favor, but he should not attempt to steal glory from his betters."), #Lothar-Aleifr
  ("npc10_personalityclash2_speech_b", "In that last battle, as always, he keeps singing and praising himself as the glorious commander that lead us all to victory, fame, and fortune. I am sorry, but if he is our leader instead of you, I am ready to go find my fortune somewhere else."), #Ceawlin-Brian
  ("npc11_personalityclash2_speech_b", "As far as I know he is an exiled man, that will never find peace, nor truly be allowed to return to his homeland. This is all because he was unable to obey his King. Well, if he can't obey even his rightful King, what says that he shall obey you? Please, don't take me wrong my dear -- for I would obey to you in any of your desires, I am even more loyal to you than I am to God --, but I think he is dangerous to all of us. I think you had best be rid of him."), #Gwenllian-Frioc
  ("npc12_personalityclash2_speech_b", "Warlord, if that man knew the slightest thing about medical matters, he would know that one should never undermine a patient's confidence in his medic, particularly not during a complicated operation. He should stick to military matters only. If you would be kind enough to dismiss him from this shield-wall, you would be doing all of us a great service."), #Orosio-Agasicles
  ("npc13_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He keeps saying that I better watch my back, for someday he will stick his lance deep into my dark Visigothic heart. So I told him that surely he must have killed his brother because he found out that he was conceived during a very brutal Visigothic raid of his father's house. He has sworn to kill me in the next battle. You better keep a close eye on this fratricidal fool."), #Liuva-Bodero
  ("npc14_personalityclash2_speech_b", "In our last battle, while I was singing about the many battles that your leadership alongside my courage allowed us all to emerge victorious from, he spit to the ground and told me to shut my arrogant mouth. If this man does not understand the legendary character of our feats, than he should not be allowed to share our glory and fortune."), #Brian-Ceawlin
  ("npc15_personalityclash2_speech_b", "{s11} responded that Hippocrates was an 'antiquated know-nothing', incomparable to the knowledge of Galenus. Warlord, no true medic would have such disrespect for the great masters of the past. I do not believe you should employ such an obvious impostor."), #Agasicles-Orosio
  ("npc16_personalityclash2_speech_b", "This awful man has openly declared that he follows the pagan gods of old, and that the teachings of Christ are nothing more than the babblings of weak men. He even made an absurd remark suggesting that I, a holy priest, brought us all bad luck with my 'gibberish preaching'. If you have no intention of leading all of your men to Hell, this Angle should be immediately sent to his afterlife."), #Aedh-Osmund
  ("npc_bashe_personalityclash2_speech_b", "When all the dust settled, {s11} turned on me and told me not to 'tempt the wrath of the Heavens' with my 'hubris.' I responded that he should care about the men he coldly killed after the battle is over, which I think angers the Gods a lot more than battlefield small talk. Then {s11} turned red like a virgin's face and would have struck me had I not artfully dodged out of his away. Tell him to lighten up, will you?"),
  ("npc_sange_personalityclash2_speech_b", "When all the dust settled, {s11} turned on me and told me not to 'tempt the wrath of the Heavens' with my 'hubris.' I responded that she should care about the men she coldly killed after the battle is over, which I think angers the Gods a lot more than battlefield small talk. Then {s11} turned red like a virgin's face and would have struck me had I not artfully dodged out of her away. Tell him to lighten up, will you?"),
