  ("npc1_kingsupport_1", "That's a great idea, Chief. All these Britons and Saxons and landed nobles who rule now, with their prisons and gibbets and scaffolds, the whippings and brandings and hangings for any man who might be driven by the crying of his children to steal a loaf of bread, or maybe a horse -- Britannia deserves something better."), #Osmund
  ("npc2_kingsupport_1", "Well, warlord -- I'd support you. I think you'd give Britannia the kind of enlightened rule which it has long needed."), #Aleifr
  ("npc3_kingsupport_1", "Well, my {lord/lady} -- I would worry for you. Our histories tell us that power tends to corrupt. But in the end, I am comforted by the mercy and judgment you have shown as warlord of this shield-wall."), #Eithne
  ("npc4_kingsupport_1", "Well, dryhten, I think that you would be the kind of {king/queen} that well-born gentlemen such as myself would be proud to follow into battle..."), #Athrwys
  ("npc5_kingsupport_1", "A fine idea - you have shown that you know how to govern men. Mind that you govern them justly, though..."), #Frioc
  ("npc6_kingsupport_1", "I cannot judge the legal merits of your claim. However, I think that unlike the other kings here, you have the capacity to unify this land -- and that would put a stop to these endless wars, between kingdom and kingdom, noble and noble, and brother and brother, that have brought us all into disgrace in the eyes of gods."), #Bodero
  ("npc7_kingsupport_1", "Aye -- you'll do well. You know how to correctly treat trackers, Picts, and women."), #Bridei
  ("npc8_kingsupport_1", "The saga of Beowulf tells us that a man who does great deeds, beyond those of the other men of his time, may claim a throne for himself. I'd say that you could make that claim."), #Siwi
  ("npc9_kingsupport_1", "Very good, dryhten. I'm a Frank by blood, but Dagobert I never stood for me when I was cheated of my inheritance. So I don't owe him anything, and I would be more than happy to have you as my {king/queen}."), #Lothar
  ("npc10_kingsupport_1", "Well, warlord, I suppose Britannia and Hibernia really need a powerful king, since Britons and Mercians are but weaklings and complete idiots, and the Saxons, incomprehensibly, can't seem to unite and conquer the whole islands..."),#Ceawlin
  ("npc11_kingsupport_1", "Why, that's a fine idea, {handsome/beauty}! I suppose I shall have to learn to call you 'Majesty', or 'Your Grace', then..."), #Gwenllian
  ("npc12_kingsupport_1", "I am sure that you would make a fine king, warlord. I flatter myself that I am a good judge of character, and you have demonstrated a capacity for compassion that far exceeds that of these others who call themselves monarchs."), #Orosio
  ("npc13_kingsupport_1", "Well, sir, the heavens have instituted a hierarchy in this world, and normally I would have no truck with usurpation. But I also think that the Brythonic kings of this land are a weak and sorry lot, not worthy the name of king, and that circumstance leaves the crown free to be taken by a better ruler, such as yourself."), #Liuva
  ("npc14_kingsupport_1", "That would be a fine thing, {sir/my lady}! Many are the tales of kings which have proven their worthiness to wear a crown through valor and courage. Perhaps you know the tale of Cu Chulainn, whose bravery and feats of arms are unparalleled in neither Hibernia nor Britannia. A splendid tale!"), #Brian
  ("npc15_kingsupport_1", "Well, you pay your men on time, when you can, generally speaking. That's the best qualification for kingship there is, in my book. You show some respect for the rights of others."), #Agasicles
  ("npc16_kingsupport_1", "It seems to me that you hear my words, and that your soul stirs in the face of Christ's teachings. Yes, I am sure that God not only approves, but is also planning your ascension as a rightful king for the sinful people of Britannia and Hibernia."), #Aedh
  ("npc_bashe_kingsupport_1", "Why not, warlord? I mean, in this war-torn and rainy island, you would be as good a King as any of those self-proclaimed conquerors that roam the fields stealing cattle and burning villages."), 
  ("npc_sange_kingsupport_1", "Why not, warlord? I mean, in this war-torn and rainy island, you would be as good a King as any of those self-proclaimed conquerors that roam the fields stealing cattle and burning villages."), 
