  ("npc_enchantress_kingsupport_1", "Why not, warlord? I mean, in this war-torn and rainy island, you would be as good a King as any of those self-proclaimed conquerors that roam the fields stealing cattle and burning villages."), 

  
  ("npc1_kingsupport_2", "Sure would, chief. But let me tell you what might bring others to your cause -- particularly us poor folk. They tell us that in the old days, the great Roman lords -- they were called governors, or maybe senators, I can't remember -- would, upon ascending to power, issue amnesty for all but the worst prisoners in the land's dungeons, giving people a second chance to make something of themselves -- like you gave me a chance for employment when no one else would."), #Osmund
  ("npc2_kingsupport_2", "Most of the lords of this land -- well, let's just say that they never held a scillinga that they didn't collect as rent or take as pillage. You, on the other hand, have some experience of commerce and trade, of the effort and risk involved in making sure that men don't go hungry in Cantwareburh while there's a glut of grain in Lundenwic, to give an example.... If you like, warlord, I reckon I could find some support for you among the merchants and stockers of this realm."), #Aleifr
  ("npc3_kingsupport_2", "I would, my {lord/lady}. But I would ask you to establish at least a minimal amount of rights to slaves, as well as a recognized procedure for them to buy their own freedom. You know I have been a slave, and we are the most abused people in the land. Slaves really need to be protected by a rightful and fair ruler."), #Eithne
  ("npc4_kingsupport_2", "Of course, warlord. The trick is now to get others to follow you. As you know, one's lineage is a great determinant of one's worthiness. Perhaps you have a long-lost ancestor of whom you have not told me, who, maybe, even fought alongside some of the heroes of Y Goddodin?"), #Athrwys
  ("npc5_kingsupport_2", "Ay, Frioc, I would. But there is something I should say, on behalf of men that have been wronged like myself. There must be a way for feuding nobles to have their disputes rightfully solved without bloodshed. I lost everything I cherished in life because the only honorable option my king had left me was to murder my enemies. There should be some kind of law, some kind of... common law, to settle down this kind of feud, or, maybe, any kind of dispute. That law would be based on the uses and customs of the land."), #Frioc
  ("npc6_kingsupport_2", "I would. I would tell anyone who listens of your deeds on behalf of the weak and helpless, of your ability to lead men against great odds and triumph, and tell them that if you were to become {king/queen}, there would be one law and one peace -- from the Pictish highlands to the Irish woods, from the lowlands to the southern shore. But you must promise me that our first war will be against those damn Visigoths and their putrid kings and nobles."), #Bodero
  ("npc7_kingsupport_2", "Yes, warlord, I would. A {king/queen}'s duty is to adequately respect all men and women that serve under his banner. You have proven more than able to do this, for, to you, the hunter and the tracker, the woman and the Pict, are as important as the warrior and the soldier, as the man and the Briton."), #Bridei
  ("npc8_kingsupport_2", "I would -- on one condition. You'd be king in Lundenwic or Cantwareburh or wherever you want to rule, but after you are installed in your hall, and your rule is unchallenged throughout the land, you will help me conquer my own Frisian throne, and we shall be as brothers to one another, both with their own realm."), #Siwi
  ("npc9_kingsupport_2", "I would, warlord, and others would too. But here's what I think -- you need to show the noble lords that you'll uphold their ancient rights. Right now, Britannia's a mess -- the lord owns the land, except it's the king who owns the forest, but the city has the right to levee tax at its gates, and the commons can use the pastures on odd Tuesdays, except in Pictland, where there is not much order at all. So I say you make things simple, like it was in the old days before even the Romans conquered Britannia -- first the {king/sovereign}, then the lords, then everyone else."), #Lothar
  ("npc10_kingsupport_2", "Certainly, dryhten. But I'd ask that you consider a thought of mine. If you became {king/queen}, then I'd ask you open your court to the Saxon nobility only, and leave out Britons and Mercians. They are weak, fragile and cowardly, and their only place in your kingdom should be as peasants, servants or slaves."), #Ceawlin
  ("npc11_kingsupport_2", "Of course, I would! I am sure, by the way you act, command and fight, also by the way you walk, and speak and love... that you are the only man honorable enough to become what only King Arthur once was: 'Penteyrnedd yr Ynys hon', or 'Chief of the Lords of this Island'."), #Gwenllian
  ("npc12_kingsupport_2", "Of course, warlord.  But if I have learned anything in my travels in this land, it is that Britons, Saxons, Mercians, and all else are sticklers for tradition. Everything must be done as it was done in the days of the Roman Empire -- even though not more than one in a hundred of them can read enough Latin to understand the imperial chronicles! Din Eidyn merchants marry their daughters according to the 'imperial' rite. Seals-Ey cattle herders churn 'imperial' butter. And of course, every king must be crowned according to 'imperial' law."), #Orosio
  ("npc13_kingsupport_2", "I would indeed, sir. I think you can unite this land, and then we'll be able to raise an army such as Britannia has never seen -- Saxons, Angles, Picts, Jutes, Goidels and even Britons, all together in one strong and invincible shield-wall. We will travel to the continent in strong sea vessels to subdue all the lands that the Roman Emperors once held sway -- and Britannia will be the birthplace of a restored Roman Empire!"), #Liuva
  ("npc14_kingsupport_2", "Of course, my {lord/lady}. Also, when claiming a throne, it does not hurt to be the subject of an epic poem, recited around campfires and hearthfires, describing one's deeds. As you no doubt know, I fancy myself a fair crafter of couplets. You could be as famous as Cu Chulainn, if only you let me sing of your deeds."), #Brian
  ("npc15_kingsupport_2", "I would. People might say that perhaps you don't have royal blood in your veins. But as far as I've seen, royal blood makes you a skinflint. Kings and nobles will take out loans or commission building projects without half a thought to how they're ever going to pay back all those commoners who expect to eat after an honest day's work. If you ask me, an honest tongue makes a {man/woman} a {king/queen}, not a fancy pedigree."), #Agasicles
  ("npc16_kingsupport_2", "Of course. I see that you plan to search and destroy any remnant of heresy and paganism from these islands. I see that you will only rest when there is no trace of the Demon in the heart of your subjects, when every man, woman and child will have only the Holy Bible as their guide, as correctly interpreted by a priest. Is your soul so pure as to intend as I say?"), #Aedh
  ("npc_bashe_kingsupport_2", "Of course, my {lord/lady}. I very well remember how you rescued me in that dark tavern, and gave me a new life. I shall travel the land, telling people how you can bring hope to even the most desperate man."), 
