  ("npc1_kingsupport_3", "If I could go about this land for a few weeks, telling the common folk that you will give amnesty to their kinfolk like the Roman -- ... hmn, consuls, I think -- of old -- well, they would start talking of you as a rightful King, and that would pave your way to the throne. Shall I do that, chief?"), #Osmund
  ("npc2_kingsupport_2", "If you like, warlord, I can take a few weeks to visit the guildhalls and harbors where I have contacts, and explain to them that, in you, they will have a {king/ruler} who will check the rapacious nobles, who, with their tariffs and taxes, would strangle commerce for the sake of a few extra scillingas to spend on their wars and their feasts. What do you say to that, warlord?"), #Aleifr
  ("npc3_kingsupport_3", "If you were to protect the poor slaves, even slave girls, I am sure most of the common people would see you as a kind and just {king/queen}. So, if you can give me a few weeks, I will travel the countryside, telling every poor man and woman that fear enslavement due to debt or war, that under your rule they would still have some protection and rights."), #Eithne
  ("npc4_kingsupport_3", "Yes -- I think I have heard of that line. In fact, I can envision {his/her} entire genealogy. If you give me leave, 'Majesty', I shall travel about the villages and castles of Britannia and Hibernia over the next several weeks, spreading word of your royal birth. Of course, I would hope that you would remember your faithful subject, when it comes to distributing lands; and I also expect you to help me find my father, after you are a crowned and powerful {king/queen}."), #Athrwys
  ("npc5_kingsupport_3", "Anyway, {lord/lady}, if I could take a few weeks to let the men of Britannia and Hibernia know that when you are {king/queen} you will institute a common law, based on tradition and customs, to resolve the disputes within the realm, be they about nobles or commoners. I am pretty sure they will all be more than happy to support your claim, since you will bring unified justice to all the lands under your rule."), #Frioc
  ("npc6_kingsupport_3", "Very well. Although I am now a stranger to my family, I have entered many a noble's hall in your train, and I reckon I would be welcome again. I shall go about this land and tell the nobles that when you are {king/queen}, you will strive your hardest to protect the weak and to crush discord, so that no man will raise his hand against another with impunity, and one day, perhaps, Britannia will rule over all the lands that are unrightfully under Visigothic sway."), #Bodero.
  ("npc7_kingsupport_3", "I'll tell you what, warlord. Give me a few weeks and I'll go to some of the villages -- stinking hovels that they are, but, anyways, I'll tell the people there that once you unify this land, every man and woman, of every profession and business, will be equally treated and respected when at your service. This way, all will reckon you as a {man/woman} whose claim to the throne is backed up by fairness and justice."), #Bridei
  ("npc8_kingsupport_3", "Good! Then give me a few weeks and I'll go about the courts of this land, letting it be known that you're like the legendary warriors of old, and that your strength, courage, prowess and ability alone are more than enough to back up your claim to the throne. Everyone shall speak of you as the new Beowulf, the successor of Arthur himself, the only one capable of bringing peace to this troubled land."), #Siwi
  ("npc9_kingsupport_3", "It's perfectly sensible, {sir/madame} -- and we'll be free of those cursed merchants' audiences and petitions and scrolls that take up all of my time and yours, when we should both be out fighting for the glory of your kingdom. Give me leave and I'll spread word among the noble lords of this land that you're here to restore the old ways, and I'll bet there will plenty who will follow you into battle."), #Lothar
  ("npc10_kingsupport_3", "Well then, dryhten, give me leave for a few weeks and I can go about this land, letting every Saxon noble know that Britannia and Hibernia will belong to them, and to them only, when you are their king. I am certain many of them will be more than happy to join your cause, to support a man with such good judgment of people and nobility."), #Ceawlin
  ("npc11_kingsupport_3", "Then, even though it will hurt me more than anything else, let me be apart from you for some time. I will travel the land speaking of your great deeds, both in war and love. I will tell how you are like Arthur himself, and no one else than you deserves to be 'Penteyrnedd yr Ynys hon'. There's many where I come from who are waiting for a just ruler, able to finally expel the Saxons, and they will start to think of you as that {man/woman}. Give me a few weeks -- even though it will hurt you too, I know -- and I'll reckon I can have quite a few expecting you to be their next {king/queen}."), #Gwenllian
  ("npc12_kingsupport_3", "But you know what? There was no 'imperial' law when it came to the crown. Sometimes one emperor handed the empire to his son. Sometimes he split it between his generals. Sometimes one emperor murdered the last. There's no right 'Roman' way to crown a {king/king or queen}, and thus it makes sense that the crown should go to the one most fit to govern -- which would be you, naturally. Give me a couple of weeks, and I'll write a tract which proves it and find a copyist to post a version in every tavern in the land. What do you say to that idea, warlord?"), #Orosio
  ("npc13_kingsupport_3", "Give me leave for a few weeks, {sir/madame}, and I will let all the worthy men of this land know that you are the one to unite not just Britannia, but all the older Imperial dominions. For according to my thinking, no one should be {king/king or queen} here unless they have the capacity to rule the entirety of the former Roman Empire -- and you alone have demonstrated such a capacity, {sir/madame}."), #Liuva
  ("npc14_kingsupport_3", "Then give me leave for a few weeks, oh gallant one, and I will spin such a tale as would stir even the dullest heart, inspiring admiration for your virtues, compassion for your hardships, and indignation at those who would stand in your way -- for you are a new Cu Chulainn, ready to make the whole world bend to your will. I assume, of course, that I would be able to take a certain amount of poetic license with the details, like when you single handedly defeated that lost Fomorian army the other day?"), #Brian
  ("npc15_kingsupport_3", "I'm glad you think so. Here's what I suggest. I know men that depend on their salaries, men like me, who've been shafted and shaken down until they can't take it anymore. Here's what I'll tell them -- you're honest. You respect the merchants. You'll pay your debts. You won't beggar your subjects."), #Agasicles
  ("npc16_kingsupport_3", "Give me leave for a few weeks, and I'll do a little tour to every church, abbey and monastery in Britannia and Hibernia. The whole Church will know that you plan to exterminate once and for all the darkness that still lingers around, outside the holiness of Christanity. Every man that truthfully fears God, and every good Christian will then support you as God's legitimately appointed ruler. What do you say to that?"), #Aedh
  ("npc_bashe_kingsupport_3", "Give me leave for a few weeks. If people start to see you as a glimmer of hope in these dark times, even a faint one, it will surely be easier for them to accept you as a rightful ruler. What do you say to that, warlord?"), 
