  ("npc1_kingsupport_objection", "Chief -- you've given leave to Lothar to go tell the nobles that they will have rights over pasture, market, and forest? I can't say I like that. Give him his way, and he'll set up gibbets in every village in the land, where there will dangle some poor sod like me who thought he might pick up a bow, head to the woods and put a bit of meat on his table."), #Osmund-Lothar
  ("npc2_kingsupport_objection", "Hum, warlord. I believe you told Siwi that after you are king of Britannia and Hibernia, you will help him to conquer the throne of Frisia. I don't think this is a good idea at all. Frisia is a good place for trade, and great riches can be made there. You would be much better off seeking to trade with that land, rather than looting and destroying their riches during the war. I really hope that Siwi misunderstood you, sir."), #Aleifr-Siwi
  ("npc3_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord -- Bridei has set off on some sort of expedition, which she says that you countenanced. She says that she will go about the villages of this land, telling the poor villagers that once you are {king/queen}, you intend to treat every man and woman, of any profession, as equals. Then I asked her about slaves, and she said that slaves are not equal to anyone, and deserve nothing more than whippings and beatings. I really hope you have not said that to her, have you?"), #Eithne-Bridei
  ("npc4_kingsupport_objection", "Dryhten. Agasicles has set off on a journey, telling the merchants that you claim the throne because you know how to balance your accounts. That's nonsense. Nobles and kings fight and rule. If they had to haggle over wages and overruns with every passing vagabond who ever did a scrap of work on their estates, then there would be nothing but disorder and chaos."), #Athrwys-Agasicles
  ("npc5_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord -- I overhead what you told Eithne. But I wonder -- if you give too much rights and protection to slaves, no one will want to have slaves. Of course, it is pretty possible to live without one, but most rich people really enjoy having one or two slaves to help with the housework. Nobles also have many, many uses for slaves and slave girls. So, you better not expect rich people and nobles to support you in this matter. This is most inconvenient for someone that seeks to be king, in my opinion."), #Frioc-Eithne
  ("npc6_kingsupport_objection", "I understand that you have dispatched Athrwys to fabricate a claim of royal descent. I have to tell you, dryhten -- I do not think that the Heavens will smile on such an attempt to take the throne by fraud, even if it is with good intentions."), #Bodero-Athrwys
  ("npc7_kingsupport_objection", "I have heard what you told Ceawlin, about splitting Britannia and Hibernia with Saxon nobles only. I specially heard the part where he said that Picts are only good as peasants or slaves. This is ridiculous - the Pictish warriors will tear your kingdom apart in days if you refuse to share land with them. I really hope you have not agreed with this and that this non sense is coming only from that squat head of Ceawlin's."), #Bridei-Ceawlin
  ("npc8_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord -- you have told Bodero that once you are king, your first war will be against the Visigoths to the south. This is not right. You should first help me to conquer Frisia and to install myself there as king. Then, maybe, we could both march together against the Visigoths, and share the spoils of the war. But our priority should be the invasion of Frisia."), #Siwi-Bodero
  ("npc9_kingsupport_objection", "{Sir/Madame} -- it is with great regret that I have learned that you have told Frioc that you plan to institute some kind of common law to govern the legal disputes in your kingdom. This makes no sense at all, since it is common knowledge that the only true fit to an enlightened realm is the Roman Imperial Law. Even the weak Dagobert I, King of the Franks, tries to impose the Roman Law whenever and wherever possible. You should follow his example."), #Lothar-Frioc  
  ("npc10_kingsupport_objection", "I hear that you've told Liuva that once you are {king/queen} you will assemble an army composed of warriors from every nation, intent on restoring the borders of the old Roman Empire. This is completely nonsensical. Only a true and pure Saxon army has any chance of achieving the glory of the ancient Romans. No army with Britons in its ranks will ever be able to conquer the continent. Don't expect me to help your wars if you try to put Saxons and Britons side by side in your 'imperial' plans."), #Ceawlin-Liuva
  ("npc11_kingsupport_objection", "I hear that Brian is off to sing and spin tales of your glory and fame, how you are just like Cu Chulainn. This is a very bad omen, my dear, for that Irish hero had a very tragic death, and also died very young. If you compare your fate to his, maybe the gods will smile upon the resemblance, and twist your fate to a similar ending. That would break my heart {handsome/beauty}, for then we would be split apart much sooner than we deserve..."), #Gwenllian-Brian
  ("npc12_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord. I hear that you've gone and made Aedh, of all people, some sort of ambassador to the Church. This preacher is nothing more than a crazy man, a fanatic. He already told me that once your kingdom is established, any kind of medical research will be forbidden, because he claims that in the Old Testament, it says that research on the human body is against the will of God. If you follow his advice, Britannia and Hibernia will surely fall in a dark age of ignorance and fear. Enough, I have said my piece."), #Orosio-Aedh
  ("npc13_kingsupport_objection", "I understand that you've sent your man Osmund to proclaim to all Britannia and Hibernia that you intend to free all the miscreants of this land upon your accession to the throne. What a foul idea... Men must be governed, dryhten -- with whips and chains and the noose, if necessary. You'll find that out the hard way if you become {king/queen}, I'll warrant."), #Liuva-Osmund
  ("npc14_kingsupport_objection", "Oh valiant one -- I hear that you have given leave to Orosio to produce some testily-worded dissertation that undermines everything the people of this land hold dear, and accuses the old emperors of murder and usurpation. Warlord -- I know as a bard that people must have heroes to emulate, and a golden age to restore. Will you create a kingdom in which cynics and scholars tell us what we must believe? I can think of nothing more dull."), #Brian-Orosio
  ("npc15_kingsupport_objection", "I understand that you've given leave to Gwenllian to spread some nonsense about you being the new 'Penteyrnedd yr Ynys hon'. I just want to say that, as an educated man, I find it disturbing that you would resort to legends and superstitions to back your claim. Village men and women will believe one thing one day, another thing the next. Now a horoscope, properly cast by an astrologer with a reputation to uphold, might tell you something worth knowing, but those are hard to find in our age of fear and ignorance."), #Agasicles-Gwenllian
  ("npc16_kingsupport_objection", "I hear that Aleifr's gone off to sing a pretty song to the merchants, of how you'll hand them Britannia on a silver platter for them to feast upon, smack their lips, and suck the marrow from the bones. I hope that's just a tale you're telling. Trade and commerce are evil practices, explicitly forbidden by God and Christ. A merchant feasts upon nothing, for he gains his money not from his own work and sweat, but only for taking the time to bring goods from one place to the other. But time belongs to God alone, and it's an awful sin to profit from abusing time and God's generosity."), #Aedh-Aleifr
  ("npc_bashe_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord -- I cannot agree with the arguments you allowed to be said in your name for the sake of your future as King. They are wrong, terribly wrong. And you know it. I am sorry to speak my mind in this rude tone, but I could no longer keep my mouth shut in face of such iniquity."), 
  ("npc_sange_kingsupport_objection", "Warlord -- I cannot agree with the arguments you allowed to be said in your name for the sake of your future as King. They are wrong, terribly wrong. And you know it. I am sorry to speak my mind in this rude tone, but I could no longer keep my mouth shut in face of such iniquity."), 
