  ("npc1_fief_acceptance", "You'd make me lord of {s17}, chief? Well, that would be the kindest thing that anyone has ever done for me in a long time. Heh. I'll make the most of it -- you can count on that. I have to say, though -- I'm not sure how the other lords of this realm will react, when they find old Osmund in their august company."), #Osmund
  ("npc2_fief_acceptance", "{s17} as a fief? Well, I've always thought in terms of buying and selling goods, not in terms of governing anything. But now that you mention it, I bet I could make that place turn a fair bit of revenue. I thank you, {my Lord/my lady} -- this is a very kind turn that you have done me."), #Aleifr
  ("npc3_fief_acceptance", "{Sire/My lady}, it is most generous of you to offer me {s17}, me, an ex-slave. I would be pleased to hold it, and dedicate myself to the moral and material uplift of its inhabitants. And I will not tolerate any kind of slavery in my fief."), #Eithne
  ("npc4_fief_acceptance", "It is good of you to grant me {s17} as a fief -- and most appropriate. Proud indeed is the king who has a lord of the House of Gwawrddur as {his/her} vassal."), #Athrwys
  ("npc5_fief_acceptance", "Warlord -- I would be most pleased to hold {s17}. I will send word to Dumnonia, to my family, kinsmen, and former servants, and let them know that there is honorable gold and prestige to be earned serving under me in your armies -- and they will come flocking to fight for you!"), #Frioc
  ("npc6_fief_acceptance", "Dryhten -- I am surprised that you find me worthy to govern men, as I am just beginning to learn to govern myself. But if you indeed wish it, I would be most honored to hold {s17} in your name, and dedicate myself to the protection of those who live there, never allowing any Visigoth to settle down there alive."), #Bodero
  ("npc7_fief_acceptance", "Aye, I'll hold {s17} -- and prove all across Britannia that Picts are more than capable of ruling and governing land and men. Thank you, {sire/madame}, for this opportunity."), #Bridei
  ("npc8_fief_acceptance", "You'd make me a Ealdorman? Well, I suppose that I can postpone claiming the throne of Frisia for a little while longer, and make my great hall at {s17}. Some day, I may travel over the seas to fulfill my destiny as king of Frisia, but until then, I would be pleased to raise a shield-wall of battle-hardened warriors to fight under your banner."), #Siwi
  ("npc9_fief_acceptance", "{Sire/My lady}, I was cheated of my inheritance -- but now, with this offer of this estate, you make right what was wrong. It would give me the greatest honor to serve you, to fight for you, and to hold this land in fief to you."), #Lothar
  ("npc10_fief_acceptance", "You'd make me a lord? Well, I think you are right -- the Saxon warriors are destined to rule all of Britannia, and, if our current lords are unable to defeat the other nations, then it is natural that the most powerful warriors like myself must arise to nobility and replace the actual weak rulers."), #Ceawlin
  ("npc11_fief_acceptance", "Ay! You'd grant me a title of nobility? There can be no greater sigil of love, can there? My, the strange turns that life takes... Fancy this once-exploited and abused housewife finding love and becoming a great peer of a realm in Britannia."), #Gwenllian
  ("npc12_fief_acceptance", "Well, {sire/my lady}, I'd have you know that don't believe in the holding of land in fief to the king. Farmers and landholders should govern their own affairs, under the distant watch of the sovereign. That being said, Britannia has seen far too much bloodshed for us to turn the social order on its head right now. Give me that land and I'll endeavor to prepare it for a brighter future -- if not in this generation, than perhaps in the next."), #Orosio
  ("npc13_fief_acceptance", "You do me a great honor, dryhten. I will serve faithfully under your banner, and shall dedicate every day of my life to raise an organized army and instill some discipline upon our soldiers of Brythonic origin. Soon, with that army, we shall together submit all of Britannia and Hibernia to your rule."), #Liuva
  ("npc14_fief_acceptance", "How generous and kind of you, {sire/my lady}. Allow me to express the utmost reverence for your wisdom in selecting me. Truly, your perspicacity exceeds that of King Salomon, who could read the character of a man from a single hair of his head. Your judgment surpasses that of the Emperor Marcus Aurelius, to whom even the most prominent patricians submitted their disputes. Anyway, I accept."), #Brian
  ("npc15_fief_acceptance", "You do me a great honor, warlord. In Creta, a youngest son such as myself has few opportunities to earn a fief of his own. But here, in Britannia, there is still the chance for a man to win with his sword what was denied him by his birth! I shall hold {s17} as your vassal, and raise an army to fight for your glory and for mine."), #Agasicles
  ("npc16_fief_acceptance", "You truly fear God and respect his will. This is good. {s17} will become a center of faith and truth, and will be a powerful beacon in the dark night of paganism and heresy that still haunts Britannia and Hibernia. Be in peace, and may God be with you."), #Aedh  
  ("npc_bashe_fief_acceptance", "Well, {sir/my lady}, that's a gracious act, and marks you as the kind of monarch who can save this sorry land from the incompetence of the current batch. I suspect a lot of the noble lords around here will think that a commoner like me isn't fit to hold a fief. Well, when they see what I do with it, and what revenues I can bring in, they'll change their tune!"), 
  ("npc_sange_fief_acceptance", "Well, {sir/my lady}, that's a gracious act, and marks you as the kind of monarch who can save this sorry land from the incompetence of the current batch. I suspect a lot of the noble lords around here will think that a commoner like me isn't fit to hold a fief. Well, when they see what I do with it, and what revenues I can bring in, they'll change their tune!"), 
  ("npc_paintrain_fief_acceptance", "Oh, that's most generous of you, {sire/my lady}. I've been in and out of many a great hall or manor -- not always with the master's permission, I should add -- but I never thought I'd own one myself. Let me think... When I collect my first year's rents, what baubles shall I buy myself?"), #klethi  
  ("npc_hammertime_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_tank_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_backwoodsharry_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_deadeye_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_probulator_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_grim_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing a fief for you {sire/my lady}."), #klethi  
  ("npc_enchantress_fief_acceptance", "Oh, that's most generous of you, {sire/my lady}. I've been in and out of many a great hall or manor -- not always with the master's permission, I should add -- but I never thought I'd own one myself. Let me think... When I collect my first year's rents, what baubles shall I buy myself?"), #klethi  
  
  ("npc1_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Osmund
  ("npc2_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Aleifr
  ("npc3_woman_to_woman", "My lady, if you don't mind me saying -- I think by now you have proven yourself to be one of the great warriors of this realm. Yet strangely, no king has come forward to offer you a fief. Perhaps it is because you are a woman. No matter -- I personally believe that you will take your place among the great lords of this realm, even if you have to fight twice as long and twice as hard to receive your due!"), #Eithne
  ("npc4_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Athrwys
  ("npc5_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Frioc
  ("npc6_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Bodero
  ("npc7_woman_to_woman", "Warlord. If you don't mind me saying, you have fought long and hard against every kind of warrior in Britannia, and with their defeat, you brought great honor to yourself. You are well deserving of a fief of your own -- and I suspect that if you were not a woman, a king would have offered you one by now. That is the way of the men in this sorry land: they let us stand in the front of the battle line to take the enemy's blows, but when it comes to a division of the spoils, they expect us to head to the rear."), #Bridei
  ("npc8_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Siwi
  ("npc9_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Lothar
  ("npc10_woman_to_woman", "{!}."), #Ceawlin
  ("npc11_woman_to_woman", "My beauty, I just can't help thinking to myself -- you've made quite a name for yourself, haven't you? Fighting and marching up and down the length of the land. Why, I suspect if you were a man, some king would have offered you a fief by now. Well, you may still get what you deserve -- you'll just have to prove yourself a bit more. And I shall always be at your side."), #Gwenllian
